## Responsibility Model

| Role | Definition |
|---|---|
| OWNER | Primary accountable nucleus for the opportunity, dependency or readiness artifact. |
| SUPPORTER | Nucleus providing evidence, input, surface, review or boundary context. |
| APPROVER | Authority required before advancement, publication, implementation or execution-sensitive work. |
| EXECUTOR | Nucleus that would own real execution if a separate future request authorizes it. |
| REVIEWER | Nucleus required to review risk, architecture, governance, treasury, security or documentation impact. |
| CONSUMER | Nucleus that consumes the output or depends on the capability. |
| BLOCKER_OWNER | Nucleus responsible for resolving or explicitly accepting a blocker. |
| ESCALATION_OWNER | Nucleus or review path responsible when a dependency exceeds current readiness. |

## Readiness Model

| Score | Portfolio Label | Meaning |
|---:|---|---|
| 0 | READINESS_UNKNOWN | Evidence does not support a readiness decision. |
| 1 | READINESS_DRAFT | Draft or concept evidence exists, but it is not yet assessed. |
| 2 | READINESS_ASSESSED | Evidence and blockers are documented, but further approval or validation is required. |
| 3 | READINESS_APPROVED | Non-executive advancement is approved under documented boundaries. |
| 4 | READINESS_READY | Evidence supports next-stage planning inside the approved non-executive scope. |

## Ownership Confidence

| Confidence | Interpretation |
|---|---|
| HIGH | Ownership is explicit in STATUS, HANDOFF, registry, report or maturity evidence. |
| MEDIUM | Ownership is supported by several documents but not always stated consistently. |
| LOW | Ownership is weakly documented or mostly roadmap-derived. |
| UNKNOWN | Ownership cannot be determined from inspected evidence. |

## Readiness Gap Model

| Gap | Meaning |
|---|---|
| NO_GAP | Current non-executive scope has enough ownership/readiness evidence. |
| DOCUMENTATION_GAP | Evidence exists but is missing, stale, partial or local/unversioned. |
| VALIDATION_GAP | Validation evidence is missing, stale, partial or not comparable. |
| OWNERSHIP_GAP | Owner, approver, executor, consumer or escalation owner is ambiguous. |
| GOVERNANCE_GAP | Governance approval or policy path is required before advancement. |
| EXECUTION_BOUNDARY_GAP | Scope touches execution-sensitive behavior that remains blocked. |
| DEPENDENCY_GAP | Required dependency is not ready, not reviewed or not formally accepted. |
| BLOCKER_GAP | Blocker ownership, status or resolution path is incomplete. |

