## Ownership Ambiguities

| Ambiguity | Affected Area | Confidence | Required Resolution |
|---|---|---|---|
| Root global portfolio documentation has no versioned repository owner. | Global docs and reports | HIGH | Select a versioned documentation home or keep explicitly local/unversioned. |
| Treasury/Financial Core naming and execution ownership is distributed across Defi, Governance and Core evidence. | Defi, treasury, financial scopes | MEDIUM | Define formal treasury owner and escalation path before any fund-impacting request. |
| AxodusAPP wallet surface ownership is distinct from product execution ownership but needs stronger contract evidence. | AxodusAPP and execution-sensitive nuclei | MEDIUM | Define wallet/read-only/display contract before any wallet-adjacent planning. |
| Harmony DAO is referenced as a supporting dependency but is not represented as an Axodus nucleus. | Governance plugin opportunities | MEDIUM | Add external dependency owner documentation before plugin advancement. |
| Business product catalog records may become UI-visible through AxodusAPP, but UI ownership transfer is not yet formalized. | Business, AxodusAPP | MEDIUM | Create read-only consumer contract before UI implementation. |

## Readiness Conclusions

- Business is the portfolio planning and classification owner, not an execution owner.
- Governance, Defi/Treasury, Dex, Trading, Marketplace, Mining, Lottery, ACS and AxodusAPP retain execution-sensitive ownership for their respective domains.
- Documentation owns publication governance but cannot publish without separate authority.
- Read-only and mock/local visibility can advance through architecture/business review when no execution path is introduced.
- Execution-sensitive opportunities remain blocked until the owning nucleus and required governance/treasury/security review approve a separate future request.

## Recommended Resolution Sequence

1. CROSS-REQ-04 - Governance & Execution Boundary Review.
2. Formalize root global docs versioning/ownership.
3. Define treasury owner and escalation path for Defi/Treasury/Financial Core scopes.
4. Create read-only Business-to-AxodusAPP consumer contract before portfolio UI work.
5. Review execution-sensitive owners for ACS, Trading, Marketplace, Mining, Lottery and Dex before any L4 implementation cycle.

## Boundary Statement

This alignment does not authorize production readiness, implementation, integration, publication, governance execution, treasury movement, wallet signing, trading, DEX execution, marketplace settlement, mining payouts, lottery payouts, ACS provisioning, billing execution, production credentials or on-chain writes.

## Assessment

READINESS_OWNERSHIP_ALIGNMENT_ESTABLISHED
